    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix race condition in MAC measurement display functions\n\n### Summary\nThe telnet server measurement display functions in `telnetsrv_enb_measurements.c` access shared RAN context data structures without proper synchronization, leading to race conditions when multiple threads access measurement data concurrently. This can cause inconsistent readings or crashes when displaying MAC/PHY/PDCP measurements.\n\nThis fix adds mutex protection around all measurement data access in the eNB measurement display functions.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/ran_context.h`: Added `measur_data_mutex` to RAN_CONTEXT_t structure for protecting measurement data access\n- `common/utils/telnetsrv/telnetsrv_enb_measurements.c`: \n  - Added pthread.h include\n  - Wrapped all measurement display functions with mutex lock/unlock:\n    - `measurcmd_display_phycpu`\n    - `measurcmd_display_maccpu` \n    - `measurcmd_display_pdcpcpu`\n    - `measurcmd_display_macstats_ue`\n    - `measurcmd_display_macstats`\n    - `measurcmd_display_rlcstats`\n  - Added missing `free(rlcstats)` in `measurcmd_display_rlcstats`\n- `executables/lte-ru.c`: Added initialization of `RC.measur_data_mutex` \n- `executables/nr-ru.c`: Added initialization of `RC.measur_data_mutex`\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the race condition:\n1. Start an eNB with telnet server enabled\n2. Connect multiple telnet clients simultaneously \n3. Run `measur maccpu` or `measur phycpu` commands concurrently from different clients\n4. Observe inconsistent measurement values or segmentation faults due to concurrent access to RC data structures\n\nThe mutex protection ensures only one thread can access the shared measurement data at a time, eliminating the race condition while preserving measurement functionality.\n"
}